The paper deals with the automated migration of hierarchical data to relational tables, which is a common problem in database systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DB (Database). The paper also presents a novel programming-by-example approach, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The evaluation of the proposed technique involves experiments with real-world datasets, which is related to cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper uses machine learning techniques to automate the data transformation tasks, which is related to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
